Module it.polimi.ingsw.PSP43
Package it.polimi.ingsw.PSP43.server.controller.modelHandlers

Class WorkersHandler

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.PSP43.server.controller.modelHandlers.WorkersHandler
public class WorkersHandler
extends java.lang.Object
WorkersHandler has the tasks of keeping track of all the workers, adding new ones and changing their position. Their methods are called from the GameSession object, which has a workersHandler attribute.

    • addNewWorker

      public int addNewWorker​(Color color)
      This method adds a new worker to the existing ones. It invokes the constructor of the worker with the color chosen by its owner and with an incremental id based on the number of already existing workers.
      Parameters:
      color - color of the worker
      Returns:
      The integer representing the ID of the new worker.

    • changePosition

      public void changePosition​(Worker worker, Coord coordAfterMove)
      This method changes the coordAfterMove of a worker, checking if the move is possible and throwing an exception if not possible. It also sets the occupation boolean flags of the two involved cells.
      Parameters:
      worker - worker whose coordAfterMove is wanted to be changed
      coordAfterMove - coordAfterMove the player wants to move the worker to

    • swapPositions

      public void swapPositions​(Worker currentPlayerWorker, Worker opponentWorker)
      Method that swap the position of two workers.
      Parameters:
      currentPlayerWorker - worker owned by the player who is making the move
      opponentWorker - worker owned by an opponent and that will be used for the swap
